                            <comment id="15031095" author="ctang.ma" created="Sun, 29 Nov 2015 17:28:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The &quot;show create table&quot; output should use SERDE instead of DELIMITED for row_format and SERDEPROPERTIES for the DELIMITED properties if any. It can ensure a table with any kind of serde/fileformat to be recreated correctly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;row_format
  : DELIMITED [FIELDS TERMINATED BY &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; [ESCAPED BY &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt;]] [COLLECTION ITEMS TERMINATED BY &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt;]
        [MAP KEYS TERMINATED BY &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt;] [LINES TERMINATED BY &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt;]
        [NULL DEFINED AS &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt;]   -- (Note: Available in Hive 0.13 and later)
  | SERDE serde_name [WITH SERDEPROPERTIES (property_name=property_value, property_name=property_value, ...)]
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
